1
00:00:06.507 --> 00:00:08.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[thunder rumbling]

2
00:00:20.145 --> 00:00:21.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[man]
He's got temporal narcosis delirium.

3
00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:24.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[man on P.A.]
<i>Trauma Team 4 to Level Red.</i>

4
00:00:24.149 --> 00:00:26.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Trauma Team 4 to Level Red.</i>

5
00:00:26.443 --> 00:00:29.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans in pain]

6
00:00:32.783 --> 00:00:35.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman on P.A.]
<i>Code 4 Nursing Unit, report to Level Red.</i>

7
00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:38.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[man] No. He does have a sensor.
It's not working.

8
00:00:38.956 --> 00:00:40.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[electronic beeping]

9
00:00:40.916 --> 00:00:43.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>Negative for dysplasia,</i>
<i>viremia, necrobiosis.</i>

10
00:00:43.627 --> 00:00:45.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Please extend your arms.</i>

11
00:00:45.879 --> 00:00:50.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Species: Dralian. Identity: Gar.</i>
<i>T.C. 15. You may proceed.</i>

12
00:00:50.759 --> 00:00:51.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[electronic beeping]

13
00:00:52.511 --> 00:00:54.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughs]

14
00:00:54.972 --> 00:00:57.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chellick. Lucky I caught you.

15
00:00:57.933 --> 00:01:00.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Gar, I wish I had time to talk.

16
00:01:00.602 --> 00:01:04.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, all you have to do is listen.
I have a new supply of cytogenics.

17
00:01:04.231 --> 00:01:07.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your last supply was useless.
Expired lots, diluted samples...

18
00:01:07.985 --> 00:01:10.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I have something special this time.

19
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:12.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The latest in substandard
technology, no doubt.

20
00:01:12.656 --> 00:01:15.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, this item is far from substandard.

21
00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:18.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And as a gesture of goodwill,
I'm offering it to you first.

22
00:01:18.912 --> 00:01:20.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We don't need another neural monitor.

23
00:01:20.872 --> 00:01:23.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mm, this is much more
sophisticated than that.

24
00:01:23.458 --> 00:01:27.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure it has some ingenious use,
but I'm not interested.

25
00:01:31.133 --> 00:01:33.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please state the nature...

26
00:01:33.552 --> 00:01:35.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of the medical emergency?

27
00:03:24.871 --> 00:03:26.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where have you taken me?

28
00:03:26.456 --> 00:03:28.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a holographic construct,

29
00:03:28.333 --> 00:03:31.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
programmed with over
five million medical protocols.

30
00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:33.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I demand to be returned
to <i>Voyager</i> at once.

31
00:03:33.588 --> 00:03:34.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What's <i>Voyager?</i>

32
00:03:35.048 --> 00:03:37.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
The Federation starship
to which I'm assigned.

33
00:03:37.175 --> 00:03:38.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
This man is a kidnapper.

34
00:03:38.802 --> 00:03:41.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[scoffs] I would never offer you
stolen property.

35
00:03:41.555 --> 00:03:43.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I traded warp-grade dilithium
for this program.

36
00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:44.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What's your price?

37
00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:46.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
This negotiation is pointless.

38
00:03:46.727 --> 00:03:50.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I'm not about to perform medical services
for a pair of common thieves!

39
00:03:50.272 --> 00:03:51.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It doesn't seem to be in working order.

40
00:03:51.982 --> 00:03:53.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-[sighs]
-[electronic beeping]

41
00:03:53.275 --> 00:03:56.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Allocator] <i>Trauma victims are now</i>
<i>arriving at Emergency Intake 7.</i>

42
00:03:56.570 --> 00:03:57.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What caused their injuries?

43
00:03:57.946 --> 00:04:01.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>A generator explosion</i>
<i>at the Gammadan Mining Facility.</i>

44
00:04:01.825 --> 00:04:04.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You'd better start cooperating,
or I will dismantle your program

45
00:04:04.953 --> 00:04:06.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
and sell it off one subroutine at a time.

46
00:04:07.038 --> 00:04:09.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
When Captain Janeway discovers
what you've done...

47
00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:11.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Let's go. Clear a path.
-We're going to lose this guy.

48
00:04:11.918 --> 00:04:13.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Come on.
-Here we go.

49
00:04:13.545 --> 00:04:14.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Move!
-All right, tuck him in there.

50
00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:17.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I can't find any coagulant.
Somebody check the reserves.

51
00:04:17.549 --> 00:04:20.844 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-There are no reserves.
-This one's got grade-4 pulmonary burns.

52
00:04:21.595 --> 00:04:24.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Allocator] <i>Patient's T.C. is 4.</i>
<i>Transfer to Level Green.</i>

53
00:04:24.431 --> 00:04:29.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Level Green isn't equipped for this.
-His T.C.'s only 4. Take him to Green.

54
00:04:29.728 --> 00:04:30.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't touch that.

55
00:04:33.482 --> 00:04:36.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This patient's bleeding seriously.
He needs an immediate infusion.

56
00:04:36.735 --> 00:04:38.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are you doing?
Get away from him.

57
00:04:38.862 --> 00:04:42.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With technology this primitive,
you may as well be using leeches.

58
00:04:42.157 --> 00:04:44.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Who is this man?
-A doctor, of sorts.

59
00:04:44.868 --> 00:04:46.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I thought you were
withholding your services.

60
00:04:46.828 --> 00:04:49.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Fortunately for these patients,
I am programmed with the Hippocratic oath.

61
00:04:49.748 --> 00:04:52.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It requires me to treat anyone who's ill.

62
00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:55.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This patient needs 20 milligrams
anesthezine. Get me a hypospray.

63
00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:56.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A what?

64
00:04:56.630 --> 00:04:59.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
I'm sorry, this may hurt a little.

65
00:05:01.676 --> 00:05:03.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[patient groans]

66
00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:19.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Did you have to program that
Nausicaan guard to high stick so much?

67
00:05:19.694 --> 00:05:22.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, you play hockey,
you've got to expect a few lumps.

68
00:05:22.405 --> 00:05:23.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[sighs]

69
00:05:23.782 --> 00:05:26.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
-What are we going to tell the Doctor?
-Hmm.

70
00:05:26.618 --> 00:05:28.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You know how he feels
about our juvenile holoprograms.

71
00:05:28.912 --> 00:05:31.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Relax. I'll come up with something.

72
00:05:32.165 --> 00:05:33.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Doc.

73
00:05:33.875 --> 00:05:35.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Please state the nature
of the medical emergency.

74
00:05:35.836 --> 00:05:37.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[both sigh]

75
00:05:37.295 --> 00:05:41.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know what you're thinking,
but there's a simple explanation.

76
00:05:41.383 --> 00:05:43.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell him, Tom.

77
00:05:43.218 --> 00:05:45.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right. Well, um...

78
00:05:45.720 --> 00:05:49.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
see, Doc, we were running
these invasion scenarios

79
00:05:49.391 --> 00:05:51.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when this species of proto-humanoid--

80
00:05:51.601 --> 00:05:53.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Please state the nature
of the medical emergency.

81
00:05:54.437 --> 00:05:55.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you okay, Doc?

82
00:05:55.772 --> 00:05:59.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Please take an analgesic
and return in 24 hours.

83
00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:03.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a replicated fake.

84
00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:07.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The program running in Sick Bay
is from one of Doc's old training files.

85
00:06:08.577 --> 00:06:11.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want someone to tell me
how this snake oil salesman

86
00:06:11.872 --> 00:06:15.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
managed to evade
every security protocol on the ship.

87
00:06:15.374 --> 00:06:19.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I take full responsibility.
-I'm not interested in fault.

88
00:06:19.629 --> 00:06:21.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just want to know how it happened.

89
00:06:21.882 --> 00:06:24.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Um, Gar spent the night in Sick Bay.

90
00:06:24.551 --> 00:06:27.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He claimed to have gotten
food poisoning at dinner.

91
00:06:27.512 --> 00:06:30.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He had plenty of time to learn
about the mobile emitter from the Doctor.

92
00:06:30.682 --> 00:06:33.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who I'm sure was more than willing
to extol its virtues.

93
00:06:33.643 --> 00:06:38.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Medical logs show the training file was
activated just before Gar left <i>Voyager.</i>

94
00:06:38.273 --> 00:06:40.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Scan for his ion trail,

95
00:06:40.525 --> 00:06:44.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and let's review safeguards for accessing
low-security files, shall we, Mr. Tuvok?

96
00:06:47.198 --> 00:06:51.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, don't blame Tuvok
for what happened. It was my fault.

97
00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:52.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How so?

98
00:06:52.329 --> 00:06:55.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Gar kept complaining
how bland his dinner was,

99
00:06:55.498 --> 00:06:59.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so I added a few exotic spices.

100
00:06:59.586 --> 00:07:01.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure I see your point.

101
00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:04.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was trying so hard
to create something he liked

102
00:07:04.090 --> 00:07:06.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that I didn't take his alien
physiology into account.

103
00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:11.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Everyone's assuming he faked his illness,
but I might have really made him sick.

104
00:07:12.015 --> 00:07:15.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not as if your cooking
turned him into a thief.

105
00:07:15.143 --> 00:07:17.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, but if he hadn't gone to Sick Bay,

106
00:07:17.604 --> 00:07:20.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he may never have come up
with a plan to kidnap the Doctor,

107
00:07:20.815 --> 00:07:23.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
much less have the opportunity to do it.

108
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:25.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In my experience, Neelix,

109
00:07:25.195 --> 00:07:27.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
men like Gar have no trouble
finding opportunities

110
00:07:27.447 --> 00:07:29.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to take advantage of other people.

111
00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:32.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I just hope there's something
I can do to help find the Doctor.

112
00:07:33.078 --> 00:07:37.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, when and if that opportunity arises,
I'm sure you'll make the most of it.

113
00:07:50.095 --> 00:07:53.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] That was the most impressive
cortical bypass I've ever seen.

114
00:07:53.264 --> 00:07:55.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's just a question
of possessing the basic skills.

115
00:07:55.684 --> 00:07:58.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah, if I had basic skills like yours,
they'd move me up to Level Blue.

116
00:07:58.311 --> 00:07:59.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Take this patient to Yellow.

117
00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:03.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You seem a little low on resources here.
If I could contact my medical staff,

118
00:08:03.358 --> 00:08:05.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I might be able to get you
some additional supplies.

119
00:08:05.694 --> 00:08:08.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Communication is usually restricted, but
the Allocator might give you clearance.

120
00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:11.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Good. Where can I find him?
-Uh, the Allocator isn't a "him."

121
00:08:11.866 --> 00:08:13.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's our main computer.

122
00:08:13.493 --> 00:08:15.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Well...
-[coughing]

123
00:08:15.829 --> 00:08:17.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps it could establish
a communications link

124
00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:18.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with <i>Voyager's </i>main computer.

125
00:08:18.957 --> 00:08:21.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] You'll have to submit
a formal request to Chellick

126
00:08:21.251 --> 00:08:24.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and support it
with Form 83-W in triplicate.

127
00:08:24.462 --> 00:08:26.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[coughing continues]
-Even then...

128
00:08:27.215 --> 00:08:29.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why hasn't this patient been treated yet?

129
00:08:30.552 --> 00:08:32.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's waiting for proton imaging.

130
00:08:32.887 --> 00:08:35.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are a lot of other people
ahead of him.

131
00:08:35.306 --> 00:08:37.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's nice to see someone knows
what's going on.

132
00:08:38.018 --> 00:08:39.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What's your name?
-Tebbis.

133
00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:42.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Tebbis,
this doesn't look too serious.

134
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:44.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, it's just a little
osteal extravasation.

135
00:08:45.734 --> 00:08:47.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excellent diagnosis.

136
00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:49.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope to be a doctor someday.

137
00:08:49.279 --> 00:08:50.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

138
00:08:50.488 --> 00:08:52.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I hope your working conditions
are better than these.

139
00:08:52.824 --> 00:08:55.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It wouldn't be so bad
if they'd let us listen to music.

140
00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:58.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It would certainly improve my mood.

141
00:08:58.329 --> 00:09:00.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not just that,
but music has great healing power.

142
00:09:01.958 --> 00:09:03.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I couldn't agree with you more.

143
00:09:03.752 --> 00:09:06.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[groans]
-Uh, exhale slowly.

144
00:09:06.921 --> 00:09:08.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[exhales]

145
00:09:08.089 --> 00:09:12.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Can't you give him a neural blocker?
-He's already had his allocation.

146
00:09:12.218 --> 00:09:14.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[low rhythmic beeping]

147
00:09:17.098 --> 00:09:20.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The leg injury isn't all I'm picking up.
He's got some kind of systemic disease.

148
00:09:20.769 --> 00:09:24.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a chromo-viral infection.
We have 12 cases down here.

149
00:09:25.774 --> 00:09:28.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-He's in the final stage.
-Is there an established treatment?

150
00:09:28.693 --> 00:09:30.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Cytoglobin injections.

151
00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:35.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These scans don't show
any cytoglobin in his bloodstream.

152
00:09:35.366 --> 00:09:37.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-He hasn't been given any.
-Why not?

153
00:09:37.827 --> 00:09:41.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-He doesn't have a high enough T.C.
-"T.C."? What's that?

154
00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:45.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah, there you are. I'm happy to report
that I've acquired your program from Gar.

155
00:09:46.002 --> 00:09:48.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Please come with me.
-I will not.

156
00:09:48.379 --> 00:09:50.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
May I remind you
I'm being illegally detained?

157
00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:53.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or hasn't the rule of law
reached this society yet?

158
00:09:54.135 --> 00:09:56.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We follow the Allocator's rules,

159
00:09:56.721 --> 00:10:00.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and it's determined that your services
are required on Level Blue.

160
00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:05.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, please, Doctor, the Allocator knows
which patients need help the most.

161
00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:12.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

162
00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:17.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Level Blue is your critical care area,
I presume.

163
00:10:17.742 --> 00:10:19.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Level Blue is the area
where it's most critical

164
00:10:19.828 --> 00:10:21.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that we provide excellent care.

165
00:10:21.496 --> 00:10:23.039 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens]

166
00:10:35.510 --> 00:10:38.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
These patients will be
your chief responsibility from now on.

167
00:10:39.514 --> 00:10:41.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do whatever you can
to make them well.

168
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:52.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why are these patients
getting preferential treatment?

169
00:10:52.402 --> 00:10:54.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They have a higher T.C. than the others.

170
00:10:54.612 --> 00:10:57.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Indulge me. What's T.C.?

171
00:10:57.198 --> 00:10:58.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Treatment Coefficient.

172
00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Allocator assigns one
to every patient.

173
00:11:00.994 --> 00:11:04.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It determines the level of care
they receive.

174
00:11:04.372 --> 00:11:07.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is this coefficient derived?

175
00:11:07.208 --> 00:11:11.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Through a complex formula that involves
profession, skills, accomplishments.

176
00:11:12.046 --> 00:11:14.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How is any of that relevant
to medical treatment?

177
00:11:15.216 --> 00:11:18.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
An agricultural engineer is obviously
more important than a waste processor.

178
00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:21.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Important to whom?
-Society.

179
00:11:22.390 --> 00:11:25.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When your resources are limited,
you have to prioritize.

180
00:11:25.435 --> 00:11:29.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, you base treatment on whether
patients have particular abilities?

181
00:11:30.565 --> 00:11:33.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's much more complicated than that.

182
00:11:33.359 --> 00:11:35.987 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Allocator assesses
the entire individual.

183
00:11:36.070 --> 00:11:38.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And reduces his life to a number.

184
00:11:39.032 --> 00:11:42.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It may seem impersonal, but it's what
the Dinaali have contracted us to do.

185
00:11:42.243 --> 00:11:43.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chellick's people are known
throughout the sector

186
00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:46.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for their administrative skills.

187
00:11:46.289 --> 00:11:49.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Before they came here,
we were a dying race.

188
00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:51.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Eco-disasters, famine...

189
00:11:51.127 --> 00:11:56.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dr. Dysek, Chief of Medicine.
The medical hologram I told you about.

190
00:11:56.132 --> 00:11:59.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you in charge of what passes
for care on Level Red?

191
00:11:59.552 --> 00:12:02.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because those people are suffering.

192
00:12:02.263 --> 00:12:06.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Intriguing technology.
Can we use him to treat patients yet?

193
00:12:06.517 --> 00:12:07.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's what he's here for.

194
00:12:08.645 --> 00:12:12.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In some societies, it's considered rude
to refer to someone in the third person

195
00:12:12.357 --> 00:12:14.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
while he's standing in front of you.

196
00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sure you'll make good use of him.

197
00:12:26.204 --> 00:12:29.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The warp trail ends here.
Gar should be directly ahead.

198
00:12:29.374 --> 00:12:31.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All stop.

199
00:12:31.376 --> 00:12:32.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Red Alert.

200
00:12:33.044 --> 00:12:34.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On screen.

201
00:12:36.798 --> 00:12:38.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's emitting a false warp signature.

202
00:12:40.426 --> 00:12:42.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looks like we've underestimated
Mr. Gar again.

203
00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:43.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now what?

204
00:12:44.555 --> 00:12:47.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-There may be another way to find him.
-What do you have in mind?

205
00:12:48.059 --> 00:12:52.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He traded us high-grade iridium,
which has a very brief half-life.

206
00:12:52.522 --> 00:12:54.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His ship is slow.

207
00:12:54.315 --> 00:12:58.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Logic suggests he acquired the substance
within a radius of three light-years.

208
00:12:59.028 --> 00:13:01.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Cross-reference our sensor logs
and long-range scans.

209
00:13:03.992 --> 00:13:06.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Two planets,
no atmosphere or technology,

210
00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:08.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a T-class nebula...

211
00:13:09.038 --> 00:13:10.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here's something.

212
00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:13.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
An asteroid with approximately
200 humanoid life signs,

213
00:13:13.835 --> 00:13:15.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
subterranean structures.

214
00:13:15.586 --> 00:13:17.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sounds like a mining operation.

215
00:13:17.463 --> 00:13:19.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If that's where Mr. Gar
acquired the iridium,

216
00:13:19.882 --> 00:13:21.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
they may be able to help us find him.

217
00:13:22.552 --> 00:13:24.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tom, how fast can you get us there?

218
00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:25.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Less than two hours.

219
00:13:26.014 --> 00:13:27.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do it.

220
00:13:32.979 --> 00:13:35.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-We're being hailed.
-Open a channel.

221
00:13:37.191 --> 00:13:39.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I want my iridium back now.</i>

222
00:13:39.986 --> 00:13:41.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I beg your pardon?

223
00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:43.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I've scanned your ship.</i>
<i>I know you've got it on board.</i>

224
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:47.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, we obtained it
from a man called Gar, a merchant--

225
00:13:47.368 --> 00:13:49.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You mean thief.</i>

226
00:13:49.787 --> 00:13:51.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, you have had
the pleasure of meeting him.

227
00:13:51.830 --> 00:13:55.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He was here two days ago.</i>
<i>He sold us 3,000 induction units.</i>

228
00:13:55.585 --> 00:13:59.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He was gone a day before we realized</i>
<i>he'd also stolen 20 kilos of ore.</i>

229
00:13:59.464 --> 00:14:01.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[scoffs]

230
00:14:01.674 --> 00:14:04.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had a similar experience.
Maybe we can help each other.

231
00:14:05.345 --> 00:14:06.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>How?</i>

232
00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:09.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have any idea
where we might find him?

233
00:14:09.766 --> 00:14:11.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Will you return my iridium?</i>

234
00:14:11.976 --> 00:14:16.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By all means, but Gar only traded us
half of what he stole from you.

235
00:14:16.564 --> 00:14:18.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
However, we might be able
to get the rest of it back.

236
00:14:19.484 --> 00:14:22.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>All I can tell you</i>
<i>is that the induction units came</i>

237
00:14:22.195 --> 00:14:23.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>from a planetoid called Velos.</i>

238
00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:25.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

239
00:14:29.035 --> 00:14:30.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You may go.

240
00:14:30.703 --> 00:14:32.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your surgical technique is impressive.

241
00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:35.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, you've obviously had
experience with cellular repair.

242
00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:38.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact, I've done
extensive research on the subject.

243
00:14:38.961 --> 00:14:43.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd be happy to share it with you, but
we'll have to contact <i>Voyager </i>to get it.

244
00:14:43.257 --> 00:14:47.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll have to discuss that with Chellick.
He authorizes all communications.

245
00:14:48.971 --> 00:14:51.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's time for this patient's
next injection.

246
00:14:51.140 --> 00:14:56.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Requesting one cytoglobin injection
for patient B-3, priority Blue-7 gamma.

247
00:14:56.479 --> 00:14:59.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator]
<i>One cytoglobin injection authorized.</i>

248
00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:06.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Does this patient have
a chromo-viral infection?

249
00:15:06.989 --> 00:15:08.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Why?

250
00:15:08.616 --> 00:15:10.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was told cytoglobin is the standard
treatment for that disease.

251
00:15:11.994 --> 00:15:14.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Cytoglobin also prevents arterial aging.

252
00:15:15.540 --> 00:15:17.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Will that be all?

253
00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:19.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You may go.

254
00:15:20.211 --> 00:15:22.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This patient's arteries
appear to be healthy.

255
00:15:22.171 --> 00:15:27.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At the moment, but daily injections
increase life expectancy up to 40%.

256
00:15:27.677 --> 00:15:30.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We prescribe them
for all Level Blue patients.

257
00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:33.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just saw a boy
on Level Red who's dying.

258
00:15:33.599 --> 00:15:35.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This medicine could save his life.

259
00:15:35.893 --> 00:15:38.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This woman is a chief engineer
of an irrigation facility

260
00:15:38.312 --> 00:15:40.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which provides water
to half the subcontinent.

261
00:15:40.606 --> 00:15:42.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, her life is more valuable?

262
00:15:42.692 --> 00:15:45.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Keeping her healthy
contributes to our survival.

263
00:15:45.486 --> 00:15:47.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can you say the same
for the boy on Level Red?

264
00:15:47.572 --> 00:15:50.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who knows what he'll accomplish
if he has the chance?

265
00:15:50.533 --> 00:15:53.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If he becomes more valuable
to society, his T.C. will rise,

266
00:15:53.494 --> 00:15:54.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and then he'll receive better treatment.

267
00:15:55.079 --> 00:15:56.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He may not be around long enough.

268
00:15:57.206 --> 00:15:59.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry he's sick,

269
00:15:59.250 --> 00:16:00.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but our society is much better off

270
00:16:00.835 --> 00:16:03.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
since we began following
the Allocator's protocols.

271
00:16:07.383 --> 00:16:08.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Some of you are.

272
00:16:14.891 --> 00:16:18.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I never expected to see you again.
-Why do you say that?

273
00:16:18.186 --> 00:16:22.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Level Blue is much more prestigious.
-Prestige is the least of my concerns.

274
00:16:22.648 --> 00:16:25.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How is he?
-Not well.

275
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:30.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

276
00:16:30.656 --> 00:16:34.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-His condition's deteriorated so rapidly.
-His coenzyme allotment's been reduced.

277
00:16:35.077 --> 00:16:37.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] Are we here to help
these people or kill them?

278
00:16:37.622 --> 00:16:40.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His T.C. is just too low.

279
00:16:40.791 --> 00:16:43.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Maybe we can raise it.
-That's not possible.

280
00:16:43.669 --> 00:16:47.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it's purely a function of statistics,
we can simply input more data.

281
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:49.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-We're not authorized to do--
-Voje.

282
00:16:49.884 --> 00:16:51.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When you look
at your patient lying there,

283
00:16:51.594 --> 00:16:56.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you have to ask yourself,
"What can I do? What must I do?"

284
00:16:57.308 --> 00:17:00.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can amend his database
to include additional skills.

285
00:17:01.062 --> 00:17:04.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Such as?
-His extensive knowledge of neutronics.

286
00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:06.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He doesn't know anything
about neutronics.

287
00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:08.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can say he does.

288
00:17:08.319 --> 00:17:10.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's the harm in trying?

289
00:17:14.700 --> 00:17:20.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Amend patient R-12's T.C.
to include an expertise in neutronics.

290
00:17:20.248 --> 00:17:23.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator]
<i>Unable to verify. Amendment denied.</i>

291
00:17:23.668 --> 00:17:25.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You see?

292
00:17:25.419 --> 00:17:27.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[weakly] Hello.
-Lie still.

293
00:17:28.923 --> 00:17:30.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

294
00:17:30.216 --> 00:17:32.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Trying to get you
the proper medication.

295
00:17:33.761 --> 00:17:37.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're wasting time you could
be spending with other patients.

296
00:17:38.015 --> 00:17:40.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have as much right
to treatment as anyone.

297
00:17:42.103 --> 00:17:43.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not your fault.

298
00:17:45.898 --> 00:17:47.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's nothing you can do.

299
00:17:59.579 --> 00:18:01.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Nurse.
-Yes, Doctor?

300
00:18:01.372 --> 00:18:05.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why hasn't this patient received
her additional cytoglobin injection?

301
00:18:05.084 --> 00:18:06.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Additional?

302
00:18:06.168 --> 00:18:09.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you'd examine her chart,
you'd see that I've increased her dosage.

303
00:18:09.547 --> 00:18:12.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Dr. Dysek didn't say anything--
-Dr. Dysek is at home with his family.

304
00:18:12.633 --> 00:18:16.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would you like me to contact him so you
can explain why you're not doing your job?

305
00:18:16.929 --> 00:18:18.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, Doctor.

306
00:18:19.932 --> 00:18:25.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Requesting one cytoglobin injection
for patient B-3, priority Blue-7 gamma.

307
00:18:25.896 --> 00:18:28.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator]
<i>One cytoglobin injection authorized.</i>

308
00:18:31.819 --> 00:18:33.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll do it myself.

309
00:18:35.364 --> 00:18:37.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can I assist you?

310
00:18:39.285 --> 00:18:40.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You may go.

311
00:18:49.420 --> 00:18:52.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[people groaning]

312
00:18:52.673 --> 00:18:54.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[people coughing]

313
00:19:00.890 --> 00:19:05.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[pained groaning]

314
00:19:06.437 --> 00:19:08.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

315
00:19:08.397 --> 00:19:11.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[pained groaning]

316
00:19:11.192 --> 00:19:12.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man grunts]

317
00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:14.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

318
00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:16.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

319
00:19:24.830 --> 00:19:26.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

320
00:19:35.174 --> 00:19:38.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He convinced me to let him take</i>
<i>the induction units on consignment.</i>

321
00:19:38.469 --> 00:19:42.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That was more than ten days ago.</i>
<i>I haven't heard from him since.</i>

322
00:19:42.807 --> 00:19:45.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You appear to be
an experienced merchant, Mr. Kipp.

323
00:19:45.434 --> 00:19:47.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why would you trust someone like Gar?

324
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:49.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He came highly recommended.</i>

325
00:19:49.897 --> 00:19:50.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By whom?

326
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:55.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>A buyer I know. He said he's been</i>
<i>trading with Gar for years.</i>

327
00:19:55.277 --> 00:19:57.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know where
we can find this buyer?

328
00:19:57.655 --> 00:20:01.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Yes, Captain. I am the fool</i>
<i>who said that Gar could be trusted.</i>

329
00:20:02.368 --> 00:20:04.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sounds like you've changed your mind.

330
00:20:04.495 --> 00:20:07.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] <i>I should have known</i>
<i>it was a mistake, but...</i>

331
00:20:07.873 --> 00:20:12.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Well... you see, I have never</i>
<i>been able to say no to my wife.</i>

332
00:20:13.045 --> 00:20:14.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What does she have to do with it?

333
00:20:15.005 --> 00:20:18.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Well, she's the one who asked me</i>
<i>to recommend Gar.</i>

334
00:20:18.134 --> 00:20:19.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then she must know him well.

335
00:20:20.886 --> 00:20:23.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>They're... friends.</i>

336
00:20:24.014 --> 00:20:25.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
May we speak with her?

337
00:20:26.142 --> 00:20:28.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>She's, uh...</i>

338
00:20:28.144 --> 00:20:29.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>She's not here.</i>

339
00:20:30.438 --> 00:20:32.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you know where we might find her?

340
00:20:33.899 --> 00:20:35.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[voice breaking]
<i>She left me.</i>

341
00:20:38.112 --> 00:20:40.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>You're a woman. You saw my husband</i>
<i>with your own eyes.</i>

342
00:20:41.031 --> 00:20:44.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Overweight, depressed...</i>
<i>You would have left him, too,</i>

343
00:20:44.994 --> 00:20:48.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>especially if you had met</i>
<i>someone as exciting as Gar.</i>

344
00:20:48.914 --> 00:20:51.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, he's very exciting.

345
00:20:51.751 --> 00:20:55.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That's why you're looking for him,</i>
<i>isn't it? You want him for yourself.</i>

346
00:20:55.588 --> 00:20:58.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I assure you, I have no romantic
interest in him whatsoever.

347
00:20:58.549 --> 00:21:00.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Why? Not good enough for you?</i>

348
00:21:01.343 --> 00:21:04.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, it's not that. It's just that...

349
00:21:07.516 --> 00:21:09.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I already have a man.

350
00:21:12.688 --> 00:21:15.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have a business opportunity
for Mr. Gar,

351
00:21:15.858 --> 00:21:18.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
one that will expire
if we don't find him soon.

352
00:21:19.945 --> 00:21:23.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He's on his way to the gambling</i>
<i>tournament on Selek IV.</i>

353
00:21:23.240 --> 00:21:26.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>When you see him,</i>
<i>tell him to hurry home.</i>

354
00:21:26.494 --> 00:21:27.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[transmission ends]

355
00:21:29.580 --> 00:21:30.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

356
00:21:46.222 --> 00:21:47.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How are you feeling?

357
00:21:49.558 --> 00:21:51.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Better.

358
00:21:51.101 --> 00:21:53.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's what happens
when you get the proper treatment.

359
00:21:57.733 --> 00:21:59.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I'm not authorized
to receive cytoglobin.

360
00:21:59.819 --> 00:22:01.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You are now.

361
00:22:01.278 --> 00:22:04.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll need several more injections,
but you can expect a complete recovery.

362
00:22:05.616 --> 00:22:08.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whatever you did, they'll find out.

363
00:22:08.285 --> 00:22:09.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They'll punish you.

364
00:22:09.620 --> 00:22:11.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're assuming
I've done something illicit.

365
00:22:11.831 --> 00:22:13.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Didn't you?
-Of course not.

366
00:22:13.457 --> 00:22:15.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I simply had a talk with Chellick,

367
00:22:15.292 --> 00:22:17.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
explained to him
what a bright young man you are,

368
00:22:17.461 --> 00:22:20.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and he had the Allocator
recalculate your T.C.

369
00:22:21.423 --> 00:22:23.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've never met a doctor like you.

370
00:22:23.092 --> 00:22:27.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well... it's not hard to stand out when
the general level of competence is so low.

371
00:22:27.847 --> 00:22:31.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are patients on this level
who deserve a higher T.C. than I do.

372
00:22:32.059 --> 00:22:33.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Could you talk to Chellick about them?

373
00:22:41.527 --> 00:22:43.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
Thank you.

374
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:47.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

375
00:22:50.703 --> 00:22:52.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah, Voje.

376
00:22:52.370 --> 00:22:53.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You're not busy, are you?
-Well, actually--

377
00:22:53.998 --> 00:22:56.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good. I want you to help me
dispense these injections.

378
00:22:56.458 --> 00:22:59.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Where did you get the cytoglobin?
-Level Blue. Where else?

379
00:22:59.587 --> 00:23:00.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You stole it?

380
00:23:00.671 --> 00:23:03.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd prefer to think of it
as "reallocation."

381
00:23:03.257 --> 00:23:05.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're going to treat
every chromo-virus patient on this level.

382
00:23:05.383 --> 00:23:07.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have any idea
what kind of trouble we could get into?

383
00:23:07.803 --> 00:23:10.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"We?" Then you will help me.

384
00:23:10.598 --> 00:23:14.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No! Absolutely not!
Modifying data files was bad enough.

385
00:23:14.310 --> 00:23:18.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I certainly wouldn't want you
to do anything to compromise your ethics.

386
00:23:18.314 --> 00:23:19.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Tebbis]
I'll help you.

387
00:23:21.233 --> 00:23:23.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You should be in bed.
-Actually, now that he's improving,

388
00:23:24.069 --> 00:23:25.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a little activity will do him good.

389
00:23:25.946 --> 00:23:29.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can go back to doing...
whatever you were doing.

390
00:23:37.249 --> 00:23:41.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The best place to inject him is here,
in the lateral artery.

391
00:23:46.175 --> 00:23:47.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excellent work!

392
00:23:47.968 --> 00:23:50.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's nice to see someone in this hospital
has a future as a healer.

393
00:23:50.721 --> 00:23:53.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] If we each take
a third of the patients,

394
00:23:53.431 --> 00:23:56.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
maybe we can finish
before someone catches us.

395
00:24:04.193 --> 00:24:07.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who do you think you are, prescribing
unnecessary medications for my patients?

396
00:24:08.072 --> 00:24:09.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It wasn't unnecessary.

397
00:24:09.490 --> 00:24:13.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you believe that, you're incompetent,
or perhaps malfunctioning.

398
00:24:15.162 --> 00:24:19.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was simply trying to increase
our allocation of resources.

399
00:24:19.917 --> 00:24:22.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What are you talking about?
-I did some checking.

400
00:24:22.294 --> 00:24:27.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Last month, Level Blue's total
medication requests were down by 6%.

401
00:24:27.549 --> 00:24:30.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Because our cure rate was higher.
-Exactly.

402
00:24:30.219 --> 00:24:32.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because you performed
so efficiently last month,

403
00:24:32.721 --> 00:24:37.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Allocator will determine
you're able to do with less next month.

404
00:24:37.685 --> 00:24:42.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we don't order more medication now,
we may not get it when we need it.

405
00:24:42.731 --> 00:24:44.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Think about it, Doctor.

406
00:24:44.775 --> 00:24:49.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you don't have the proper resources,
your cure rate could go down.

407
00:24:49.405 --> 00:24:50.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[whispering]
If that happens,

408
00:24:50.739 --> 00:24:53.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Allocator may assign you
to a lower level.

409
00:24:53.450 --> 00:24:54.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

410
00:24:54.785 --> 00:24:58.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are we having a problem
with our newest piece of technology?

411
00:24:59.957 --> 00:25:00.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually...

412
00:25:02.876 --> 00:25:06.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he seems to be learning
the system quite well.

413
00:25:15.264 --> 00:25:19.184 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh. Three of the patients we injected
are practically virus-free.

414
00:25:19.268 --> 00:25:20.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you expect?

415
00:25:21.478 --> 00:25:26.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Um, maybe we could "reallocate"
other medications, treat more patients.

416
00:25:26.567 --> 00:25:29.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, you're thinking like a doctor,
and to support your efforts,

417
00:25:29.737 --> 00:25:32.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've arranged for resources
from Level Blue to be diverted here

418
00:25:32.656 --> 00:25:34.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on a regular basis.

419
00:25:34.616 --> 00:25:35.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did you manage that?

420
00:25:36.076 --> 00:25:40.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let's just say, Dr. Dysek and I have
developed a professional rapport.

421
00:25:40.247 --> 00:25:41.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sometimes, I even surprise myself.

422
00:25:43.959 --> 00:25:46.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We may actually make
these people better.

423
00:25:47.046 --> 00:25:49.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That feeling you get
from healing someone...

424
00:25:49.882 --> 00:25:51.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
infectious, isn't it?

425
00:25:55.763 --> 00:25:57.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did you get that?

426
00:25:57.139 --> 00:26:00.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One of the technicians was going
to recycle it because it wasn't working,

427
00:26:00.558 --> 00:26:02.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I think I fixed it.

428
00:26:02.311 --> 00:26:03.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm.

429
00:26:03.479 --> 00:26:04.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

430
00:26:05.022 --> 00:26:07.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Seems to be in good condition.

431
00:26:07.232 --> 00:26:08.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And so do you.

432
00:26:08.317 --> 00:26:10.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You'll be well enough to leave soon.

433
00:26:11.528 --> 00:26:13.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Couldn't you say I'm still sick?

434
00:26:14.740 --> 00:26:16.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't you want to go home?

435
00:26:16.116 --> 00:26:19.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I do, they'll send me to work
in the refinery with my father.

436
00:26:19.536 --> 00:26:21.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What about school?
Your medical training?

437
00:26:22.748 --> 00:26:24.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I would never be authorized for that.

438
00:26:24.500 --> 00:26:26.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's right.

439
00:26:26.376 --> 00:26:30.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I stay here, you can teach me,
and I can help you treat your patients.

440
00:26:33.634 --> 00:26:36.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not planning on being here
that long myself.

441
00:26:38.596 --> 00:26:40.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then I can help Dr. Voje.

442
00:26:45.187 --> 00:26:46.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll see what we can do.

443
00:26:51.985 --> 00:26:54.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have picked up Gar's ship,
directly ahead.

444
00:26:54.863 --> 00:26:56.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Again?

445
00:26:56.698 --> 00:26:58.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Tuvok]
I'm reading his bio-signs.

446
00:26:58.242 --> 00:27:00.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Any sign of the Doctor
or his emitter?

447
00:27:00.577 --> 00:27:02.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Not yet.
-Should I hail Gar?

448
00:27:02.913 --> 00:27:06.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we let him know we're here,
he may try to slip away.

449
00:27:06.291 --> 00:27:07.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We could drop out of warp
at close range

450
00:27:07.876 --> 00:27:10.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and grab him before he knows
what's happening.

451
00:27:10.295 --> 00:27:11.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like it.

452
00:27:11.629 --> 00:27:13.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tom, Tuvok.

453
00:27:20.848 --> 00:27:21.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's hailing.

454
00:27:22.307 --> 00:27:25.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess we put him in the mood to talk.
On screen.

455
00:27:26.436 --> 00:27:29.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I thought we were friends, Captain.</i>
<i>Why am I being treated this way?</i>

456
00:27:30.065 --> 00:27:31.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I think I deserve better.</i>

457
00:27:31.775 --> 00:27:34.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Where's our Doctor?
<i>-I have no idea.</i>

458
00:27:34.403 --> 00:27:36.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I certainly hope</i>
<i>nothing's happened to him.</i>

459
00:27:36.864 --> 00:27:39.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Scans are complete.
Neither the mobile emitter

460
00:27:39.867 --> 00:27:42.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
nor the Doctor's program
are aboard Gar's ship.

461
00:27:42.744 --> 00:27:44.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Well, of course they're not.</i>

462
00:27:49.877 --> 00:27:52.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's trying to destabilize
the tractor beam with a feedback pulse.

463
00:27:53.005 --> 00:27:55.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Compensating.
-Don't bother, Harry.

464
00:27:58.343 --> 00:27:59.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just beam him to the brig.

465
00:28:11.773 --> 00:28:13.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[whispering]
Tebbis, wake up.

466
00:28:14.943 --> 00:28:16.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Time to make our rounds.

467
00:28:20.824 --> 00:28:22.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Locate patient R-12.

468
00:28:22.700 --> 00:28:25.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>Patient R-12 has been</i>
<i>transferred to Level White.</i>

469
00:28:28.040 --> 00:28:30.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Tebbis has been moved.
-I know.

470
00:28:30.083 --> 00:28:32.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What's Level White?
Some kind of patient recovery area?

471
00:28:33.754 --> 00:28:34.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's the morgue.

472
00:28:47.476 --> 00:28:50.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I demand an explanation
for the death of that boy.

473
00:28:51.772 --> 00:28:55.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm responsible for thousands of patients.
You'll have to be more specific.

474
00:28:56.151 --> 00:28:57.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His name was Tebbis.

475
00:28:59.071 --> 00:29:00.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Patient R-12!

476
00:29:03.909 --> 00:29:06.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Acute chromo-viral disease.

477
00:29:06.119 --> 00:29:07.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He was recovering.

478
00:29:07.913 --> 00:29:09.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Apparently, he developed complications.

479
00:29:09.748 --> 00:29:11.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What kind of complications?

480
00:29:11.917 --> 00:29:14.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A secondary infection.
It spread rapidly.

481
00:29:14.878 --> 00:29:16.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How was it treated?
-It wasn't.

482
00:29:16.922 --> 00:29:19.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The patient had exceeded
his medication allotment.

483
00:29:19.383 --> 00:29:22.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It seems someone had given him
unauthorized injections.

484
00:29:25.180 --> 00:29:27.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did you think I wouldn't find out?

485
00:29:33.272 --> 00:29:35.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't you have any ethical standards?

486
00:29:35.899 --> 00:29:38.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are hardly in a position
to speak to me of ethics.

487
00:29:38.860 --> 00:29:42.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Lying, stealing...
Any other crimes you wish to confess?

488
00:29:42.364 --> 00:29:44.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was trying to save lives.

489
00:29:44.491 --> 00:29:47.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I am trying to save a society!

490
00:29:47.452 --> 00:29:50.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you really think patient R-12
is going to help me do that?

491
00:29:50.706 --> 00:29:52.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His name was Tebbis.

492
00:29:52.249 --> 00:29:55.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He wasn't contributing.
He was a drain on resources.

493
00:29:55.127 --> 00:29:56.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're not just rationing
health care here.

494
00:29:57.004 --> 00:29:58.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're getting rid of the sick
and the weak!

495
00:29:59.006 --> 00:30:01.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the boy had been fit,
he would have survived.

496
00:30:01.174 --> 00:30:03.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why don't you just put a phaser
to their heads?

497
00:30:04.511 --> 00:30:06.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're healers, not killers.

498
00:30:06.138 --> 00:30:07.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

499
00:30:08.682 --> 00:30:12.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I'm going to expose you.
-To whom? The people who employ me?

500
00:30:13.687 --> 00:30:17.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They brought me here to make
the hard choices they don't want to make.

501
00:30:17.399 --> 00:30:20.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
From now on,
I'm restricting you to Level Blue.

502
00:30:20.736 --> 00:30:22.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've done enough damage on Red.

503
00:30:22.446 --> 00:30:26.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You mean those patients that I treated?
Yes, that was inconsiderate of me.

504
00:30:26.950 --> 00:30:30.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was. You managed to exceed their annual
medication allotment in a matter of days.

505
00:30:30.620 --> 00:30:31.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're being sent home.

506
00:30:33.081 --> 00:30:34.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They'll die!

507
00:30:34.708 --> 00:30:36.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You should have considered
the consequences of your actions.

508
00:30:37.878 --> 00:30:41.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Please, don't make them suffer
for my mistakes.

509
00:30:41.923 --> 00:30:45.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It won't happen again.
-I'm making certain of that.

510
00:30:45.510 --> 00:30:48.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
From now on, your time
will be strictly regulated.

511
00:30:48.096 --> 00:30:49.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Meaning what?

512
00:30:49.181 --> 00:30:52.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've interfaced your holo-matrix
with the Allocator.

513
00:30:52.309 --> 00:30:55.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Starting now, it will determine
where you go, when you go,

514
00:30:55.604 --> 00:30:57.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and what you do when you get there.

515
00:30:58.023 --> 00:31:01.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>The medical hologram will</i>
<i>now commence treatment on Level Blue.</i>

516
00:31:04.446 --> 00:31:07.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You have six minutes to treat patient B-3.</i>

517
00:31:14.706 --> 00:31:17.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know where he is.

518
00:31:17.125 --> 00:31:20.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not now, perhaps,
but you know where you took him.

519
00:31:20.253 --> 00:31:23.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The last time I saw him,
he was in your Sick Bay.

520
00:31:24.883 --> 00:31:29.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you refuse to cooperate, your knowledge
of his location can be extracted.

521
00:31:30.680 --> 00:31:31.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How?

522
00:31:32.516 --> 00:31:33.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A mind-meld.

523
00:31:34.851 --> 00:31:36.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's that?

524
00:31:36.561 --> 00:31:38.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
An invasive and disturbing procedure.

525
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:41.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[gulps]
-[Neelix] Dinnertime!

526
00:31:41.483 --> 00:31:44.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Neelix, I am in the middle
of an interrogation.

527
00:31:44.486 --> 00:31:47.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, you know
better than anyone

528
00:31:47.114 --> 00:31:51.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that Starfleet has strict guidelines
about allowing prisoners to eat.

529
00:31:52.702 --> 00:31:54.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very well. I'll wait.

530
00:31:58.625 --> 00:32:00.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There we are.

531
00:32:03.004 --> 00:32:05.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm glad to see you enjoying a meal.

532
00:32:05.507 --> 00:32:08.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When you got sick last time,
I thought my food was to blame,

533
00:32:08.844 --> 00:32:13.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
until I realized it was just a ruse
for you to get close to the Doctor.

534
00:32:14.808 --> 00:32:18.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I used Talaxian wormroot as the base.

535
00:32:18.270 --> 00:32:19.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

536
00:32:19.938 --> 00:32:22.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm glad you like it.
Some people react badly.

537
00:32:24.192 --> 00:32:25.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

538
00:32:25.277 --> 00:32:26.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
React how?

539
00:32:26.778 --> 00:32:28.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, dear, I hope you're not getting sick.

540
00:32:29.948 --> 00:32:33.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it's the wormroot,
it's going to get a lot worse.

541
00:32:35.036 --> 00:32:36.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What have you done to me?

542
00:32:36.621 --> 00:32:42.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The usual symptoms are abdominal spasms,
which increase in severity for 30 hours.

543
00:32:44.212 --> 00:32:45.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Forty at the most.

544
00:32:46.339 --> 00:32:49.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Tuvok to Sick Bay.
-Don't worry, Mr. Tuvok, it's not fatal.

545
00:32:49.134 --> 00:32:53.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's horribly unpleasant,
but, uh... there's an antidote.

546
00:32:53.430 --> 00:32:55.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then give it to me!

547
00:32:55.724 --> 00:33:00.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unfortunately, our Doctor is the only one
authorized to administer it.

548
00:33:01.271 --> 00:33:03.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe if you remembered
where he was...

549
00:33:03.773 --> 00:33:05.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

550
00:33:06.109 --> 00:33:08.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. Neelix...

551
00:33:08.111 --> 00:33:09.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have you deliberately
poisoned this man?

552
00:33:09.905 --> 00:33:12.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Relax. He's just having gas pains.

553
00:33:12.449 --> 00:33:14.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your actions are not only
against regulations--

554
00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:18.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Didn't I hear someone
threaten a mind-meld?

555
00:33:18.538 --> 00:33:22.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was merely trying to encourage
the suspect to be more forthcoming.

556
00:33:22.334 --> 00:33:23.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Yeah.
-[Gar groans]

557
00:33:23.793 --> 00:33:26.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think he's getting
all the encouragement he needs.

558
00:33:31.134 --> 00:33:33.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Excuse me, Doctor.
-What is it?

559
00:33:33.428 --> 00:33:35.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I need to prepare this patient
for discharge.

560
00:33:35.931 --> 00:33:38.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I'm not finished with him yet.
-But Chellick's orders are to--

561
00:33:38.391 --> 00:33:40.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are to discharge the patient
at the end of the shift!

562
00:33:40.727 --> 00:33:42.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The shift isn't over, is it?

563
00:33:42.521 --> 00:33:45.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-No, sir, but I need time in order--
-I'll tell you when he's ready.

564
00:33:45.565 --> 00:33:49.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>Dr. Voje, report to Level Blue</i>
<i>to assist Dr. Dysek in surgery.</i>

565
00:34:03.583 --> 00:34:04.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[quietly]
Voje!

566
00:34:08.755 --> 00:34:10.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I didn't realize
that any of this even existed.

567
00:34:10.840 --> 00:34:12.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I need to talk to you.
-I don't have time.

568
00:34:12.968 --> 00:34:15.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just got a message from the Allocator
that Dysek needs me.

569
00:34:15.303 --> 00:34:18.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm the one who sent for you.
I used his access codes.

570
00:34:18.390 --> 00:34:19.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

571
00:34:19.307 --> 00:34:22.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I need you to smuggle
my mobile emitter off Level Blue.

572
00:34:22.811 --> 00:34:25.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>Time has expired</i>
<i>for treatment of patient B-1.</i>

573
00:34:25.605 --> 00:34:27.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Proceed to patient B-3.</i>

574
00:34:30.860 --> 00:34:31.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

575
00:34:31.778 --> 00:34:35.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>The medical hologram</i>
<i>has one minute to treat patient B-3.</i>

576
00:34:36.032 --> 00:34:37.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to help me.

577
00:34:37.367 --> 00:34:40.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Twelve patients on Level Red are
being sent home because of you.

578
00:34:40.620 --> 00:34:44.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's why we have to hurry.
We may still be able to save them.

579
00:34:44.249 --> 00:34:45.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've already endangered my patients,

580
00:34:45.834 --> 00:34:47.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and now you're asking me
to risk my career?

581
00:34:48.044 --> 00:34:49.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why should I help you?

582
00:34:49.421 --> 00:34:52.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because I have a plan
to heal those patients.

583
00:34:52.299 --> 00:34:55.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's what doctors do. We heal.

584
00:34:55.302 --> 00:34:57.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So, choose. What kind of doctor
are you going to be?

585
00:34:57.846 --> 00:35:00.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>The medical hologram</i>
<i>has 30 seconds to deactivation.</i>

586
00:35:00.599 --> 00:35:01.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You hear that?

587
00:35:04.644 --> 00:35:05.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How can I get you off this level?

588
00:35:07.147 --> 00:35:10.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Deactivate my mobile emitter
and put it inside this selenide medkit.

589
00:35:10.650 --> 00:35:12.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It'll shield the signature.
-And then what?

590
00:35:12.944 --> 00:35:14.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take it to Level Red
and reactivate me.

591
00:35:14.904 --> 00:35:17.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] What are you going to do
once you get to Level Red?

592
00:35:17.115 --> 00:35:19.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>The medical hologram</i>
<i>has ten seconds to deactivation.</i>

593
00:35:19.951 --> 00:35:22.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's no time to explain.
You'll have to trust me.

594
00:35:43.475 --> 00:35:46.353 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suspect young Dr. Voje
helped you escape.

595
00:35:46.436 --> 00:35:48.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He had nothing to do with it.

596
00:35:48.188 --> 00:35:51.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No matter. You're becoming
far too troublesome.

597
00:35:51.358 --> 00:35:53.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm going to have
to deactivate your program.

598
00:35:55.695 --> 00:35:56.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Voje!
-[groans]

599
00:35:58.365 --> 00:36:00.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's wrong with him?

600
00:36:00.367 --> 00:36:03.536 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What are you doing?
-A little experiment in empathy.

601
00:36:03.620 --> 00:36:05.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You told me you were just developing
new treatment protocols.

602
00:36:05.955 --> 00:36:07.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A single protocol, actually.

603
00:36:07.791 --> 00:36:10.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're only making things
worse for yourself.

604
00:36:10.293 --> 00:36:12.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact,
I'm making things worse for you.

605
00:36:12.462 --> 00:36:15.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm going to make you a patient
in your own hospital.

606
00:36:18.802 --> 00:36:22.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What was in that injector?
-A neural blocker...

607
00:36:22.097 --> 00:36:24.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
combined with the same virus
that afflicted Tebbis.

608
00:36:24.974 --> 00:36:27.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I trusted you.
-And Tebbis trusted me.

609
00:36:27.811 --> 00:36:31.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You remember Tebbis, don't you?
Patient R-12?

610
00:36:31.481 --> 00:36:34.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Maybe this will jog your memory.
-[electronic beeping]

611
00:36:34.734 --> 00:36:37.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What are you doing?
-[Allocator] <i>Patient R-12.</i>

612
00:36:37.362 --> 00:36:40.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Species: Dinaal. Identity: Tebbis.</i>

613
00:36:40.990 --> 00:36:42.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is ridiculous! I'm not Tebbis!

614
00:36:43.076 --> 00:36:44.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But the Allocator thinks you are.

615
00:36:45.078 --> 00:36:46.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How did you--?
-Simple.

616
00:36:46.663 --> 00:36:49.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Allocator identifies patients
by reading blood factors.

617
00:36:49.499 --> 00:36:53.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I altered Chellick's by injecting him
with antigens from Tebbis.

618
00:36:53.253 --> 00:36:57.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, why don't we see
if we can get your condition treated?

619
00:36:57.298 --> 00:37:00.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Requesting one cytoglobin injection
for patient R-12.

620
00:37:00.135 --> 00:37:02.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[electronic beeping]
-[Allocator] <i>Treatment denied.</i>

621
00:37:02.929 --> 00:37:05.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I order you to medicate me now.

622
00:37:05.473 --> 00:37:07.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ordinarily, I would...

623
00:37:08.810 --> 00:37:11.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but if the Allocator says no...

624
00:37:11.730 --> 00:37:14.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Is this some sort of revenge?
-Not revenge.

625
00:37:15.108 --> 00:37:16.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Leverage.

626
00:37:16.609 --> 00:37:20.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want enough cytoglobin to cure
every infected patient on this level.

627
00:37:20.572 --> 00:37:22.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We don't have an adequate supply.

628
00:37:22.782 --> 00:37:24.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's plenty on Level Blue.

629
00:37:24.492 --> 00:37:27.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Where it's being used
to prevent arterial aging.

630
00:37:27.746 --> 00:37:31.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Those patients will survive without it,
but a dozen people on this level won't.

631
00:37:31.374 --> 00:37:33.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will not let them die.

632
00:37:40.300 --> 00:37:43.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Entering orbit.
-Scan for the Doctor's signature.

633
00:37:49.434 --> 00:37:51.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
He's dying.

634
00:37:51.186 --> 00:37:52.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As soon as we get the cytoglobin,

635
00:37:52.604 --> 00:37:54.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we'll be able to treat
all of the Level Red patients,

636
00:37:54.647 --> 00:37:55.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
including him.

637
00:37:56.816 --> 00:38:00.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You said it yourself. Doctors heal.
We don't make patients sick!

638
00:38:00.612 --> 00:38:02.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't know any other way
to help these people.

639
00:38:02.822 --> 00:38:04.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Chellick]
Dr. Voje...

640
00:38:07.786 --> 00:38:09.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I need the medicine now.

641
00:38:09.454 --> 00:38:14.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sir, I only have a Level Red clearance.
You know I'm not authorized.

642
00:38:14.501 --> 00:38:17.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then find someone who is.

643
00:38:27.096 --> 00:38:30.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've got him. He's aboard a vessel
above the northern continent.

644
00:38:30.975 --> 00:38:34.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Can you get a lock?
-It's not going to be easy.

645
00:38:34.187 --> 00:38:37.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His program seems to be interfaced
with the main computer.

646
00:38:37.565 --> 00:38:38.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hail the ship.

647
00:38:39.901 --> 00:38:41.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're responding, audio only.

648
00:38:41.736 --> 00:38:45.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Allocator] <i>This is </i>Hospital Ship 42.
<i>Allocation Module Alpha.</i>

649
00:38:46.074 --> 00:38:48.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is Captain Janeway
of the Starship <i>Voyager.</i>

650
00:38:48.993 --> 00:38:52.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would like to speak with someone
regarding a member of my crew

651
00:38:52.121 --> 00:38:53.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
who is aboard your vessel.

652
00:38:54.082 --> 00:38:57.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Administrator Chellick</i>
<i>is currently unavailable.</i>

653
00:38:57.126 --> 00:38:59.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then may I speak with someone else?

654
00:38:59.420 --> 00:39:03.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Only Administrator Chellick is authorized</i>
<i>to communicate with alien species.</i>

655
00:39:12.517 --> 00:39:14.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are we having a problem here?

656
00:39:14.227 --> 00:39:16.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dysek. Finally.

657
00:39:16.688 --> 00:39:19.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry. I had to tell him.

658
00:39:21.150 --> 00:39:23.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are you waiting for?
Give me the cytoglobin.

659
00:39:24.112 --> 00:39:26.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I don't think I can.
-What are you saying?

660
00:39:26.781 --> 00:39:29.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Cytoglobin isn't authorized
for Level Red patients.

661
00:39:29.492 --> 00:39:31.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Dysek!
-I don't want to break the rules.

662
00:39:31.995 --> 00:39:33.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I made the rules!

663
00:39:33.955 --> 00:39:36.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then you should be pleased
I hold them in such high regard.

664
00:39:36.791 --> 00:39:39.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry, Captain. I can't transport him
without damaging his matrix.

665
00:39:40.044 --> 00:39:41.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then you'll have to go
down there and get him.

666
00:39:42.046 --> 00:39:43.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Torres]
Aye, Captain.

667
00:39:43.381 --> 00:39:44.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chakotay.

668
00:39:49.387 --> 00:39:53.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't tell me you're allied
with this defective hologram.

669
00:39:54.017 --> 00:39:59.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, but he has given me insight into
some of the intricacies of our system.

670
00:40:00.273 --> 00:40:02.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For example, did you know

671
00:40:02.859 --> 00:40:06.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if I don't request enough resources
for Level Blue this month,

672
00:40:06.738 --> 00:40:09.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I won't get what I need next month?

673
00:40:09.115 --> 00:40:10.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

674
00:40:10.992 --> 00:40:15.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, Doctor, one way to increase
your allocation of resources on Level Blue

675
00:40:15.914 --> 00:40:18.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
would be to increase
the number of patients.

676
00:40:18.583 --> 00:40:23.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know at least a dozen people who
should be treated for... arterial aging.

677
00:40:24.130 --> 00:40:26.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Saving their lives would
be just a side effect.

678
00:40:26.466 --> 00:40:29.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hmm. Perhaps we should have them
transferred to Level Blue.

679
00:40:29.469 --> 00:40:32.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you're looking
for a second opinion, I concur.

680
00:40:32.263 --> 00:40:35.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well... Chellick, what do you think?

681
00:40:35.308 --> 00:40:36.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's absurd!

682
00:40:36.684 --> 00:40:39.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'd have to transfer you
to Level Blue as well.

683
00:40:40.021 --> 00:40:41.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You'd get your cytoglobin.

684
00:40:47.987 --> 00:40:48.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor.

685
00:40:48.988 --> 00:40:52.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It's nice to see some friendly faces.
-We're going to get you out of here.

686
00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:54.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who do we talk to about accessing
their main computer?

687
00:40:54.911 --> 00:40:58.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll be with you in a moment.
I'm with a... patient.

688
00:41:00.249 --> 00:41:02.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do we have an agreement?

689
00:41:04.671 --> 00:41:05.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

690
00:41:13.179 --> 00:41:16.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've managed to stay well
while I was away.

691
00:41:16.265 --> 00:41:17.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm giving you a clean bill of health.

692
00:41:18.017 --> 00:41:20.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You were only away four days.

693
00:41:20.228 --> 00:41:22.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A lot can happen in four days.

694
00:41:22.730 --> 00:41:25.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Injuries, infections... malfunctions.

695
00:41:25.692 --> 00:41:28.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As you said, I'm fine. Thank you.

696
00:41:28.736 --> 00:41:31.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was wondering
if you'd mind doing me a favor.

697
00:41:31.864 --> 00:41:34.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd like you to give me a checkup.

698
00:41:36.744 --> 00:41:38.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you been experiencing problems?

699
00:41:38.788 --> 00:41:44.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, but as you said,
I've been off the ship for a while,

700
00:41:44.210 --> 00:41:46.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
interfaced with an alien computer...

701
00:41:48.631 --> 00:41:52.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your program appears to be operating
within normal parameters.

702
00:41:52.260 --> 00:41:53.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

703
00:41:53.803 --> 00:41:56.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about over the past several days?

704
00:41:58.016 --> 00:42:00.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's no indication
of diminished capacity.

705
00:42:01.853 --> 00:42:05.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No problems with my ethical subroutines?

706
00:42:06.858 --> 00:42:08.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
None.

707
00:42:08.526 --> 00:42:10.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see.

708
00:42:10.987 --> 00:42:12.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You seem disappointed.

709
00:42:18.244 --> 00:42:20.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
While I was aboard that ship...

710
00:42:20.997 --> 00:42:22.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I poisoned a man.

711
00:42:22.582 --> 00:42:24.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Deliberately?
-Yes.

712
00:42:24.834 --> 00:42:28.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was trying to force him to let me
treat patients who were dying.

713
00:42:31.049 --> 00:42:34.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were prepared to sacrifice
an individual to benefit a collective.

714
00:42:35.678 --> 00:42:39.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No offense, Seven,
but I don't exactly aspire to Borg ideals.

715
00:42:43.061 --> 00:42:46.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were hoping your behavior
was the result of a malfunction.

716
00:42:49.984 --> 00:42:51.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry, Doctor,

